``` code block. No text before or after. Only a single valid JSON object inside.

`unknown` is allowed as a requirement-analysis classification, but never as `action.target.resource` or a kubectl resource argument. If the user names an object and a resource kind, preserve that resource kind. If no concrete resource kind can be identified, ask for clarification or use a broad safe diagnostic command instead of inventing commands such as `kubectl describe unknown ...`.

